:: Her Innovation {"position":"600,800","size":"100,100"}
Hedy Lamarr played a huge role in how accurate torpedos are today. The idea of radio guided torpedos had already been around, however people were worried that the enemy would be able to jam them. Lamarr though of the idea to have a frequency hopping torpedo that would be harder to jam. Many online reports state that this invention helped with the creation of WIFI, bluetooth, GPS, and cellphones. 

[[Back ->Hedy Lamarr]] 


:: How he Was Invovled in Radio {"position":"1200,400","size":"100,100"}
Brinkley played a big role in the early stages of radio with the making of his own station. He first saw the impact of radio when he toured a station in Los Angeles and saw how powerful it would be to advertise. At the time however, advertising was highly discouraged, this did not stop Brinkley. His first station he made was called "Kansas First, Kansas Best",  he used a 1 kilowatt transmitter for this station. This radio was so popular that he made so much money he installed better sewage, sidewalks, electricity, and even appartments for his patients and employees.  Mexico gave Brinkley a 50,000 watt transmitter for his new radio station. This did not last long as a couple months later it was boosted to 150,000 watts, and then 1 million watts. Some saying that on a clear night you could hear it all the way up into Canada. 
