:: Shannon / Hartley Theorem {"position":"400,400","size":"100,100"}
This theorem stated the maximum rate at which information can be transfered over a single channel depending on what type of communication it is. You would find the channel capacity, the highest rate at which data can be communicated with low error, using the Signal Power. 

[[Back->Claude Shannon]] 
<img src="https://energyzarr.typepad.com/.a/6a00e5522adbfd88340154356c483d970c-pi" style = "max-width: 100%;">  




:: Spread Spectrum Principle {"position":"500,500","size":"100,100"}
The principle of Spread Spectrum was mainky used in the military world with communications. This would spread the signal of the message over many different frequencies. Making it harder for enemies to listen in on the messages that you are sending. Also it increased the resistance of the sounds to outside noise, natural interference, and jamming.

[[back->Claude Shannon]] 
<img src="https://www.allaboutcircuits.com/uploads/articles/TB_SSRF_2.JPG" style = "max-width: 100%;">  



:: The Way he Changed How Radio Was Goverened {"position":"1100,500","size":"100,100"}
Brinkley's radio station actually made the US make a Brinkley Act in 1932. This made it to where any station live in the United States could not be connected to a transmitter in Mexico. Brinkley's radio station was connected via international phone lines to his transmittors in Mexico. 



[[Back->John Romulus Brinkley]] 


